    "stat_block": {
        "type": "stat_block",
        "subtype": "weapon",
        "text": "No one's entirely certain who developed the spoon gun, but all authorities agree that it was probably a goblin. Essentially a terrible idea in firearm form, the spoon gun is a spring-powered hand cannon with a modified grip that uses miscellaneous knives, forks, chopsticks, and spoons as ammunition. Users typically upend the entire contents of their cutlery drawer into the gun, aim it in the general direction of the foe, and hope it hits something.  \n   \n This hand cannon is a martial weapon, instead of a simple weapon. It has the scatter (5 feet) trait and uses cutlery or similar-sized objects as ammunition instead of bullets (enough cheap cutlery to fire ten shots costs 1 sp).   \n   \nBig boom guns and spoon guns are modified versions of hand cannons with potential benefits and drawbacks alike, rather than separate weapons. If you have access to the spoon gun or big boom gun modifications, you can purchase them whenever you would purchase a hand cannon, and effects that depend upon and apply to hand cannons apply to both weapons.",
        "level": 1,
        "traits": [
            {
                "name": "Uncommon",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 159,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 11",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 11,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "f31704572455b8d77a8bd97c0045fde6",
                "text": "Something of uncommon rarity requires special training or comes from a particular culture or part of the world. Some character choices give access to uncommon options, and the GM can choose to allow access for anyone. Less is known about uncommon creatures than common creatures. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creature is increased by 2.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Recall Knowledge",
                        "alt": "Recall Knowledge",
                        "game-obj": "Actions",
                        "aonid": 26
                    }
                ],
                "classes": [
                    "uncommon"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Cobbled",
                "type": "trait",
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Guns & Gears",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Guns & Gears pg. 231",
                            "alt": "Guns & Gears pg. 231",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 98
                        },
                        "page": 231,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 98
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "372f154dd17ad84ea742aacc0adc256b",
                "text": "This firearm is cobbled together and likely to misfire. No matter how well you upkeep it, on a failed attack roll, the attack misses and you must roll a DC 5 flat check. If you fail this check, the weapon misfires.",
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Goblin",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 81,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core pg. 456",
                            "alt": "Player Core pg. 456",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        },
                        "page": 456,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "2.0",
                            "alt": "2.0",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 216
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "4f7b46a2044aea5ae844a7fc8b3bbbaa",
                "text": "A creature with this trait is a small, frantic goblinoid. Goblins tend to have darkvision. An ability with this trait can be used or chosen only by goblins. A weapon with this trait is created and used by goblins.",
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ]
            },
            {
                "name": "Modular",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 271,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "Player Core 2",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "Player Core 2 pg. 274",
                            "alt": "Player Core 2 pg. 274",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 227
                        },
                        "page": 274,
                        "errata": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "1.1",
                            "alt": "1.1",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 227
                        }
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "34c8c3292092e7f05eaa086e75d06c7c",
                "text": "The weapon has multiple configurations that you can switch between using an Interact action. Typically, switching between configurations of a modular weapon allows it to deal different types of damage (listed in the trait, such as \u201cmodular B, P, or S\u201d), though it's possible for a modular weapon's description to list more complicated configurations.",
                "links": [
                    {
                        "type": "link",
                        "name": "Interact",
                        "alt": "Interact",
                        "game-obj": "Actions",
                        "aonid": 2297
                    }
                ],
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ],
                "value": "B, P, or S"
            },
            {
                "name": "Scatter",
                "type": "trait",
                "alternate_link": {
                    "type": "alternate_link",
                    "game-obj": "Traits",
                    "aonid": 413,
                    "alternate_type": "legacy"
                },
                "edition": "remastered",
                "sources": [
                    {
                        "type": "source",
                        "name": "NPC Core",
                        "link": {
                            "type": "link",
                            "name": "NPC Core pg. 50",
                            "alt": "NPC Core pg. 50",
                            "game-obj": "Sources",
                            "aonid": 236
                        },
                        "page": 50
                    }
                ],
                "game-obj": "Traits",
                "game-id": "078ebaefcfbeb6e50d1317aa9be6ee75",
                "text": "This weapon fires a cluster of pellets in a wide spray. Scatter always has an area listed with it, indicating the radius of the spray. On a hit, the primary target of attacks with a scatter weapon take the listed damage, and the target and all other creatures within the listed radius around it take 1 point of splash damage per weapon damage die, of the same type as the initial attack.",
                "classes": [
                    "trait"
                ],
                "value": "5 ft."
            }
        ],
